---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Annual Doctoral Symposium 2026 | Brenkley Doctoral College" description="Join Brenkley Doctoral College's Annual Doctoral Symposium on 24–26 November 2026 — three days of research presentations, keynotes, and networking for doctoral researchers and supervisors.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-b border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">Events 2026</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Annual Doctoral Symposium 2026</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-accent font-medium mb-4">24–26 November 2026 &mdash; Online and Newcastle upon Tyne</p>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl mx-auto">Our annual celebration of doctoral research brings together researchers, supervisors, alumni, and guests for a day of intellectual exchange, peer learning, and community. Open to all Brenkley Doctoral College researchers and invited guests.</p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap">
        <a href="/connect" class="btn-primary">Register Interest</a>
        <a href="#events" class="btn-outline">View all events</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- About the Symposium -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">About the Symposium</p>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">A Day for the Brenkley Doctoral College Research Community</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">The Brenkley Doctoral College Annual Doctoral Symposium is the centrepiece of our academic year. It is a day for researchers at all stages — from those just beginning their doctoral journey to those preparing to submit — to share their work, receive peer feedback, and connect with the wider community of practitioner-scholars.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">The 2026 Symposium runs in a hybrid format, with a live venue in Newcastle upon Tyne and a fully interactive online stream. Whether you attend in person or remotely, you will have access to the full programme, including keynotes, parallel research sessions, methods workshops, and an evening networking reception (in-person).</p>
          <p class="text-muted">Research presentations are supported and developmental — this is not a competitive conference but a community event. Feedback is constructive, facilitated by a faculty discussant, and designed to help researchers strengthen their work.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Date</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">24–26 November 2026</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Format</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Hybrid — Newcastle upon Tyne venue (TBC) and fully interactive online stream</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Who Should Attend</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">All current Brenkley Doctoral College researchers, alumni, supervisors, and invited professional guests. Applications to present welcome from Year 1 onwards.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Cost</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Free for all current Brenkley Doctoral College researchers and supervisors. Guest tickets: £95 in-person, £25 online. Alumni: complimentary online access.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Abstracts</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Submission deadline for research presentations: 1 August 2026. 300-word abstract required. All submissions reviewed by the Symposium Committee.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Programme -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-y border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Symposium Programme</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-10">Provisional Programme — 24–26 November 2026</h2>

      <!-- Day 1 -->
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 pb-2 border-b-2 border-accent">Tuesday 24th November 2026</h3>
      <div class="space-y-4 mb-12">
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">12:00</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Arrive at Event</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Head to the registration desk – register and collect your programme and lanyard/badge, and locate essential facilities like restrooms, the cloakroom, and the main presentation halls.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">13:00</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Welcome and Opening Keynote</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Prof. Stanley Oliver, Principal — Brenkley Doctoral College. Annual research community address and keynote on practitioner research in a changing world.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">14:00</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Researcher Presentations — Session A</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm"><span class="font-medium">Chair: Dr Zahra Salimi – Brenkley Doctoral College</span><br/>Parallel tracks: Leadership &amp; Organisational Change — how leaders navigate transformation, culture, and resistance in complex organisations. Three presentations per track, each with faculty discussant feedback.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">15:30</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Break &amp; Networking</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">In-person coffee and discussion. Online researchers participate in facilitated virtual networking rooms.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">16:00</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Researcher Presentations — Session B</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm"><span class="font-medium">Chair: Dr Xiaoling Wu – Edinburgh Napier University</span><br/>Parallel tracks: Education Policy &amp; Practice — research into teaching, learning, curriculum, and institutional leadership in educational settings. Three presentations per track.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">17:30</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Closing Plenary &amp; Community Discussion</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Reflections from the day, announcements, and open discussion on the future of practitioner research.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">18:00</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Evening Reception (In-Person)</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Informal drinks and networking for in-person attendees at the historic Newcastle upon Tyne venue.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Day 2 -->
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 pb-2 border-b-2 border-accent">Wednesday 25th November 2026</h3>
      <div class="space-y-4 mb-12">
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">09:00</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Alumni Keynote</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm"><span class="font-medium">Dr Mikele Grosser – Affiliation TBC</span><br/>A Brenkley Doctoral College alumnus presents the impact of their doctoral research on practice.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">10:00</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Researcher Presentations — Session C</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm"><span class="font-medium">Chair: Dr Paul Oliver – Edinburgh Napier University</span><br/>Parallel tracks: Strategy &amp; Innovation — how organisations develop competitive advantage, manage disruption, and drive innovation. Three presentations per track, each with faculty discussant feedback.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">11:30</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Break &amp; Networking</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">In-person coffee and discussion. Online researchers participate in facilitated virtual networking rooms.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">12:00</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Methods Workshop</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm"><span class="font-medium">Dr Zahra Salimi – Brenkley Doctoral College</span><br/>Annual methods focus session. 2026 theme: <em>Research Ethics in Insider Research — navigating access, positionality, and organisational politics.</em></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">13:00</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Lunch</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">In-person lunch provided at the historic Newcastle upon Tyne venue. Online participants take a break.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">14:00</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Alumni Keynote</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm"><span class="font-medium">Dr Stefanie Schulster – Affiliation TBC</span><br/>A Brenkley Doctoral College alumnus presents the impact of their doctoral research on practice.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">15:00</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Researcher Presentations — Session D</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm"><span class="font-medium">Chair: Dr Elizabeth Blower – Brenkley Doctoral College</span><br/>Parallel tracks: Workforce, Wellbeing &amp; HR — people management, employee experience, diversity, and organisational health. Three presentations per track.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">16:30</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Closing Plenary &amp; Community Discussion</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Reflections from the day, announcements, and open discussion on the future of practitioner research.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">18:00</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Evening Reception (In-Person)</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Informal drinks and networking for in-person attendees at the historic Newcastle upon Tyne venue.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Day 3 -->
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 pb-2 border-b-2 border-accent">Thursday 26th November 2026</h3>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">09:00</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Alumni Keynote</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm"><span class="font-medium">Dr Premnath K Narayanan – Affiliation TBC</span><br/>A Brenkley Doctoral College alumnus presents the impact of their doctoral research on practice.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">10:00</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Researcher Presentations — Session E</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm"><span class="font-medium">Chair: TBC</span><br/>Parallel tracks: Public Services &amp; Social Impact — research in healthcare, government, third sector, and community-facing organisations. Three presentations per track, each with faculty discussant feedback.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">11:30</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Break &amp; Networking</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">In-person coffee and discussion. Online researchers participate in facilitated virtual networking rooms.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">12:00</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Researcher Presentations — Session F</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm"><span class="font-medium">Chair: Dr Premnath K Narayanan – Affiliation TBC</span><br/>Parallel tracks: Digital Transformation &amp; Technology — the impact of AI, data, and digital systems on organisations and professional practice. Three presentations per track, each with faculty discussant feedback.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">13:00</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold">Closing Plenary &amp; Community Discussion</h4>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Reflections from the day, announcements, and open discussion on the future of practitioner research.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- All Events -->
  <section id="events" class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">2026 Events Calendar</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">All Upcoming Events</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">

        <div class="card">
          <div class="text-sm text-accent font-medium mb-1">20 May 2026</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Supervisor Workshop</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-3">A dedicated professional development day for doctoral supervisors. Themes: supporting researchers through difficulties, use of AI tools in research supervision, and managing multi-supervisor relationships. Facilitated by Dr. Zahra Salimi and external guests.</p>
          <div class="text-sm text-muted mb-4">
            <span class="font-medium">Format:</span> Online (half-day, 09:00–13:00)<br/>
            <span class="font-medium">Audience:</span> Brenkley Doctoral College supervisors and invited HE professionals<br/>
            <span class="font-medium">Cost:</span> Free for Brenkley Doctoral College supervisors / £75 external
          </div>
          <a href="/connect" class="btn-outline text-sm">Register interest</a>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="text-sm text-accent font-medium mb-1">10 June 2026</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Research Methods Webinar</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-3">Open to all Brenkley Doctoral College researchers and the wider practitioner-research community. Topic: <em>Navigating the Literature Review — from systematic search to critical synthesis.</em> Hosted by Dr. Zahra Salimi, Academic Lead for Research &amp; Enterprise, with a Q&A session.</p>
          <div class="text-sm text-muted mb-4">
            <span class="font-medium">Format:</span> Online webinar (90 minutes, 17:30–19:00)<br/>
            <span class="font-medium">Audience:</span> Open to all<br/>
            <span class="font-medium">Cost:</span> Free
          </div>
          <a href="/connect" class="btn-outline text-sm">Register interest</a>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="text-sm text-accent font-medium mb-1">24–26 November 2026</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Annual Doctoral Symposium</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-3">The flagship event of the Brenkley Doctoral College year. A full day of researcher presentations, keynotes, a methods workshop, and networking. Hybrid format — Newcastle upon Tyne venue and online stream. Abstract submissions open from 1 June.</p>
          <div class="text-sm text-muted mb-4">
            <span class="font-medium">Format:</span> Hybrid — Newcastle upon Tyne &amp; Online (full day)<br/>
            <span class="font-medium">Audience:</span> Researchers, supervisors, alumni, guests<br/>
            <span class="font-medium">Cost:</span> Free for current researchers
          </div>
          <a href="/connect" class="btn-primary text-sm">Register interest</a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-t border-border py-16 px-6 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Join the community</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">Whether you are a current researcher, prospective applicant, alumni, or interested professional — Brenkley Doctoral College events are open and welcoming. Register your interest to receive updates and invitations.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap">
        <a href="/connect" class="btn-primary">Register interest</a>
        <a href="/experience" class="btn-outline">Student experience</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
